Low-level methods for getting projects and tables from NASIS Web Reports

Source: R/get_NASISWebReport.R
get_NASISWebReport.Rd

get_NASISWebReport(): Gets a table from the "ReportData" section of specified report_name

get_NASISWebProjects(): Gets a table of project name, state, approval statu and project record ID for specified office, fiscal year and project name pattern.

get_NASISWebReport(report_name, proj_id, verbose = TRUE)

get_NASISWebProjects(msso, fy, project, verbose = TRUE)

Arguments

report_name

internal report name
proj_id

integer; Project record ID
verbose

Default: TRUE; print messages with report name and parameters?
msso

MLRA soil survey office e.g. "2-SON"
fy

Fiscal year e.g. 2020
project

Expression to match in project name e.g. "MLRA 18%"

Value

A data.frame, or (invisible) try-error if request fails
